        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(windows): add taskbar tray companion",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a native Windows taskbar tray companion under `Windows/` with repository status rows, local git state, recent GitHub lists, traffic/heatmap/changelog summaries, Actions queue/billing/runner details, rate-limit diagnostics, PR notifications, issue navigator, preferences, named account profiles, GitHub App OAuth, account-scoped Credential Manager token storage, launch-at-login, update checks, and installer packaging.\n- Add Windows build/package/smoke/Crabbox scripts and a Windows CI job.\n- Document Windows setup and the remaining parity roadmap.\n\n## Validation\n- `CRABBOX_PROVIDER=aws CRABBOX_TARGET=windows pnpm windows:crabbox`\n- Crabbox run `run_c168edc023e0`: Windows Server 10.0.20348, .NET SDK 8.0.421, `dotnet build` succeeded with 0 warnings/errors, `dotnet test` passed 50 tests, `smoke_windows.ps1` published and launched `RepoBar.Windows.exe` and verified the generated settings file.\n\n## Notes\n- This is a draft because Windows is now end-to-end build/test/smoke validated, and GitHub App OAuth plus named account profiles are implemented, but not true full macOS feature parity yet. The main remaining gap is archive-backed cache/CLI parity.\n- No screenshot attached yet; the hosted proof currently validates process launch/settings generation rather than a captured notification-area UI.\n",
